cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a new loss function for weakly-supervised learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper uses normalized cut, which is a graph-based image segmentation technique, and this connects to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions fast Bilateral filtering, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses semi-supervised learning, which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE).
